    <abstract id="Abs1">
      <sec>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <p>Mass spectrometry imaging (MSI) experiments result in complex multi-dimensional datasets, which require specialist data analysis tools.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Objectives</title>
        <p>We have developed <italic>massPix—</italic>an R package for analysing and interpreting data from MSI of lipids in tissue.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Methods</title>
        <p><italic>massPix</italic> produces single ion images, performs multivariate statistics and provides putative lipid annotations based on accurate mass matching against generated lipid libraries.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Results</title>
        <p>Classification of tissue regions with high spectral similarly can be carried out by principal components analysis (PCA) or <italic>k</italic>-means clustering.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Conclusion</title>
        <p><italic>massPix</italic> is an open-source tool for the analysis and statistical interpretation of MSI data, and is particularly useful for lipidomics applications.</p>
      </sec>
    </abstract>
